Fixes the cart subtotal sync (added in Magento 2.4.9) wrongly reloading the cart on every load
on stores that display prices INCLUDING tax.

Root cause: getCentralSubtotal() sums only `.price-excluding-tax .cart-price` row totals. The cart
row total is rendered by Magento\Tax\Block\Item\Price\Renderer as either `.price-excluding-tax` or
`.price-including-tax` depending on the "Display Prices in Shopping Cart" tax setting. On stores
displaying prices including tax the excluding-tax markup is never present, so the central subtotal
is always 0, never matches the summary subtotal, and the script AJAX-reloads the cart every time.

Fix: fall back to `.price-including-tax .cart-price` when no excluding-tax row prices exist, so the
central subtotal is computed in whichever tax basis is actually displayed. On excluding-tax stores
the fallback is never reached and behaviour is unchanged.

